oai_dc:dc.dc:title: 1792 silver Spanish real coin
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This Spanish coin was found north of Nashville, Tennessee. Such Spanish silver coins were legal tender until the 1830s and circulated widely in early middle Tennesse. It has the image of Charles IV and says "Carolus IIII - Dei Gratia - 1792" on one side. The other side has the crowned Spanish arms between the pillars of Hercules.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Tennessee State Library and Archives, Nashville, Davidson County, Tennessee
